b. Direct the Inventory Committee  to plan/strategize on how to conduct and complete the physical inventory within the prescribed period including the preparation of the PIP. Also, execute the physical count of all PPE and ensure that property records are updated and reconciled with the accounting records based on the results of the said count in order to come up with the correct PPE balances of the city; and

c. Enjoin all department heads to coordinate with the Accounting and General Services Offices and Inventory Committee to facilitate the conduct of physical count  and    the reconciliation of the PPE accounts to establish actual existence, ownership    and condition of the PPE assigned  to  their respective department/offices.

