We have recommended the following to the Local Chief Executive:
Expedite personnel movement in order to acknowledge the exemplary performance of employees by way of promotion to higher rank and thereby allowing the entry of new applicants for lower level positions;
Direct the City Human Resource Officer to publish all vacancy in accordance with Civil Service Commission Memorandum Circular No. 03, s. 2001 for more effective administration of the said offices which in turn will benefit the city as a whole.

We recommended the management to observe the following provisions of COA Circular No. 2020-006 for thee One-Time Cleansing of PPE Account Balances of the city, viz:

Items 5.0 and 6.0 - General and procedural guidelines in the conduct of physical count of PPEs;
Item 7.0          Disposition procedures for non existing
missing PPEs;
Item8.0             Procedures in derecog-nition of non-existing/missing PPE’s without available record of accountability; and Item 9.0 Accounting entries and disclosure in the Notes to the Financial Statements.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the Local Development Council during the preparation of the annual budget to include only PPAs which are feasible, specific and properly identified with target dates of execution and designate a personnel in-charge for its implementation and coordinate with the City Engineering Office (CEO) to ensure that the same are supported with POWS to ensure optimum utilization of the funds and timely and efficient implementation of development projects.
Further, to improve planning and budgeting capabilities, the CPDC:
Carefully plan and organize the project management plan;
Include in the planning and budgeting the guidelines and policies involving the implementation of PPAs approved by the Sangguniang Panlungsod;
Evaluate whether the PPAs funded from prior years’ budget are still relevant, otherwise recommend for realignment of the funds to other programs and projects which are more needed and applicable; and
Strictly monitor and evaluate PPAs’ implementation in accordance with the approved AIP pursuant to Section 476 of RA No. 7160 and provide for project support or program maintenance as mandated.
To ensure that the plans are carried out, the CPDC and City Engineer:
Clearly describe how the project will be managed and controlled in its delivery/execution phase;
Fast tract the implementation of on-going/unimplemented PPAs; and
Make sure that the timeline set for every program/project is realistic and strictly followed since the timing of execution spells out the success of a program or a project.

We recommended the management to:
Direct the LDRRMO to meticulously and judiciously prepare and implement the LDRRMFIP in accordance with the national, regional and provincial framework;
Incorporate in the current year’s LDRRMFIP the prior years’ unspent LDRRM  Funds;
Fully implement the project pending for the years 2017-2019;
Consistently prepare and submit a monthly Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRMF; and
Send two (2) or three (3) qualified personnel for sufficient trainings under the supervision of the Office of the Civil Defense until accredited as official trainor of the same office.

